propOverview:

Read Blvd. Industrial Facility is a 250,000 S.F. multi-building, multi-story manufacturing complex that has been developed since the 1960's.  Significant additions and upgrades were made to the facility in 1978, 1987, 1991, and most recently in 1995.  The buildings were designed specifically for manufacturing use and contain many built-in items including fixtures and equipment.  There are 3 entrances and exits to the facility with 3 parking lots adequately serving the complex. Adjacent neighbors are Eastman Kodak to the north, west, and south, and Holleder Industrial Park to the east.  Access to I-390 is available approximately 1 mile to the west at the intersection of Ridgeway Avenue and I-390, and Ridge Road is located less than one mile to the north.  The Greater Rochester International Airport is approximately 4 miles to the south.

334,000 SF Class A East AL Manufacturing Facility
Former Pillowtex manufacturing plant (#2).  Phenix Center I is located on a 28.4 acres campus.   Building is roughly 705' x 446' and is comprised of 324,141 sf of manufacturing area and 23,786 sf of office area (2-story). The plant is located approximately 84 miles from Montgomery, Alabama and 111 miles from Atlanta, Georgia.  It has easy access to several major highways including US Hwy. 431-280 Bypass, I-85 (24-miles) and I-185 (4-miles).
The property is also served by a Norfolk Southern rail line and has  a rail spur.
